begin_memory_text: I told her my name and she told me hers....I laughed and said usually these conversations start off with talking about doing surveys and we talked about how we like prolific
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about tv shows we like....I talk about how I like to watch shows where people are at work and they love the work they are doing
end_memory_text: I was talking in great detail about my work day yesterday and how it was a tough day at Seaworld that I had to put out fires throughout the day.
rest_of_day_open: Heading for the weekend working at Seaworld in the hot sun...it's not typical at work these days because of covid...the lack of business has everyone on  edge...I hope I get laid off to get a chance to restart and find another career. So I see it going so so at best.
critical_positive: We both enjoyed talking about the pay rate and how it's always nice to get a good opportunity to make some extra money. The conversation flow well and we had fun talking about tv shows we like. My partner explained in fine detail about the shows she liked and so did I.
critical_negative: There was not much that was an issue....There was a point where we both were unsure where the conversation was going next. That did not last long though and the other issue was talking about covid....because I feel when one explains their ideas the other good be internally thinking something different.

begin_memory_text: We started by me saying I was so glad he showed up because my last partner did not show up. Then we introduced ourselves. We talked about survey companies and how successful we have been with Prolific.
middle_memory_text: We talked about tv shows. My partner was telling me about the show called The Pickers and how they pay a fair price for items they buy, and then we touched briefly on Pawn Stars and how they were more miserly. I mentioned reality shows like the fishermen and Oak Island and said I really like them because those are things I would never do in my life. Then I asked what is his current favorite show and we talked about The Walking Dead and I talked about Supernatural.
end_memory_text: Nick pretty much handled the majority of the end of our conversation. He told a story of what happened to him at work yesterday and how he dealt with the situation and how he felt. He works at Sea World managing a couple food stalls and the ice cream stall was open yesterday when it wasn't supposed to be. So when he went over to check on product there was hardly any product left. He talked about how he solved the problem.
rest_of_day_open: Since today is Thursday the rest of my week is short. I don't have class tomorrow and I don't work, so I will most likely read a novel. I will complete a quick quiz for my psychology class tomorrow. On Saturday I am going to a corn maze with a friend and then later in the day I will be visiting with some friends outside at their new house. On Sunday I will work the sound board at church and I may do a little grocery shopping. I will work a little bit on my German homework.
critical_positive: Nick was friendly and had done conversations like this before, so it was easy to talk with him. He kept the conversation going and was mindful of the time we spent talking. I was genuinely curious about the things he was interested in and so that made the conversation continue. I felt we only had one very small moment of conversation breakdown, maybe 5-10 seconds, and then we were able to think of more to discuss.
critical_negative: Talking about COVID was a little stressful to me because it's kind of like talking about politics or religion with someone you don't know. It was a bit uncomfortable but I think we made it through that part of the conversation without having a total disagreement and we were able to move on to other topics.
